The article discusses the positive impact of the tax cuts signed into law by President Trump on small businesses and the economy. The co-owner of a rock climbing gym, Andrew Kratz, highlights how the tax savings have allowed him and other small business owners to invest in their companies and employees, including raising wages, providing bonuses and benefits, and creating more jobs. The article also mentions that the unemployment rate is the lowest it's been in nearly 50 years, there are more job openings than people seeking jobs, and the GDP is projected to grow by more than 3 percent in 2018. The corporate tax rate cut has made American businesses more competitive and has resulted in the repatriation of trillions of dollars previously held overseas. The tax cuts have also led to savings for families through the child tax credit and increased standard deduction. Overall, the article emphasizes the positive economic growth and benefits resulting from the tax cuts.